This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of quantization, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the speed and efficiency of the translation process, which could fall under the categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) if the translation involves image or video data.
